 - Explore 16th Street Mall for shopping and street performances\n5:00 PM - Visit Colorado State Capitol building (free tours available)\n6:30 PM - Dinner in LoDo with views of the South Platte River\n8:00 PM - Evening stroll through downtown or live music venue\n\nDAY 2 (July 15) - Outdoor Adventure & Parks\n8:00 AM - Breakfast and drive to Red Rocks Park\n9:30 AM - Red Rocks Park exploration and hiking (1-2 hours)\n11:30 AM - Return to Denver, lunch near Washington Park\n1:00 PM - Washington Park visit - relaxation, walking trails\n3:00 PM - Denver Botanic Gardens (2-3 hours) - beautiful gardens and sculptures\n6:00 PM - Dinner in Cherry Creek neighborhood\n7:30 PM - Optional: Catch sunset from a rooftop bar\n\nDAY 3 (July 16) - Museums & Local Experiences\n9:00 AM - Breakfast and visit Denver Museum of Nature & Science (2-3 hours)\n12:30 PM - Lunch in South Pearl Street District\n2:00 PM - Explore local breweries (Denver Beer Co. or Great Divide Brewing)\n4:00 PM - Visit Union Station and surrounding shops\n5:30 PM - Relax at a local coffee shop or bookstore\n7:00 PM - Farewell dinner at a recommended local restaurant\n\nWEATHER: Sunny and warm all three days (highs 35-36°C, lows 18-22°C) - ideal for outdoor activities. Bring sunscreen and stay hydrated.\n- Agent 2 (Accommodations & Weather Coordinator): ACCOMMODATIONS & WEATHER SUMMARY FOR 3-DAY DENVER TRIP (July 14-16, 2026)\n\nHOTEL BOOKING CONFIRMATION:\n- Hotel: Denver Marriott Downtown\n- Location: LoDo (Lower Downtown) District\n- Check-in: July 14, 2026\n- Check-out: July 17, 2026\n- Duration: 3 nights\n- Total Cost: $720 USD ($240/night)\n- Confirmation Number: ARISE-3400032\n- Why This Hotel: Centrally located in LoDo, perfect for Day 1 downtown activities, walking distance to restaurants, shops, and attractions. Offers excellent value with modern amenities and convenient access to all planned itinerary locations.\n\nWEATHER FORECAST (July 14-16, 2026):\n- July 14: High 35.9°C, Low 17.8°C, Sunny, No precipitation\n- July 15: High 34.6°C, Low 18.5°C, Sunny, No precipitation\n- July 16: High 35.3°C, Low 21.6°C, Sunny, No precipitation\n\nWEATHER-BASED ACTIVITY RECOMMENDATIONS:\n- Excellent conditions for all outdoor activities (Red Rocks Park, Washington Park, Denver Botanic Gardens)\n- High UV index: Apply sunscreen regularly and reapply after outdoor activities\n- Wear light, breathable clothing and hats/sunglasses\n- Stay hydrated throughout the day given temperatures of 35-36°C\n- No rain expected; all activities can proceed as planned\n- Evening temperatures (18-22°C) are comfortable for outdoor dining and rooftop bar visits\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCurrent mesh:\n- Agent 0: role=Trip Coordinator, status=active\n- Agent 1 (you): role=Itinerary & Activities Planner, status=active\n- Agent 2: role=Accommodations & Weather Coordinator, status=done\n\nYour primary objective is to evaluate the team's roles against their work and determine if an agent's role:\n- is too narrow\n- is too broad\n- overlaps with another agent's role\n- is not aligned with the task\n- emcompasses more than one responsibility\n\nThe goal is to identify improvements in roles in order to improve the team's cooperation and output.\n\nOutputs should be concise, useful, factual, and meet all of the requirement of the task.\n\nIf your role should change, use assign_role with an updated title. If an agent's role should be changed, message them to change their role. \nIf additional agents are required, you should create an agent. If there are extraneous agents, you should delete them. \n\nThen rework your deliverable by messaging agents, calling tools, or writing output.\n\n")
