c drive) | Driving Time: 3-4 hours\n- Route: CA-1 (Pacific Coast Highway) - one of world's most scenic drives\n- Stops & Hikes:\n  * Pfeiffer Beach (purple sand, 1 hour)\n  * McWay Falls Trail (0.8 miles, easy, 1 hour) - iconic waterfall\n  * Bixby Bridge (historic 1932 bridge, photo stop)\n  * Point Lobos State Natural Reserve (2-3 hours hiking)\n- Overnight: Monterey, California\n\n**DAY 8 (Aug 1): Monterey & Yosemite Approach**\n- Distance: 130 miles | Driving Time: 2.5 hours\n- Morning: Monterey Bay Aquarium, Cannery Row exploration\n- Route: US-101 South to CA-152 East toward Yosemite\n- Overnight: Mariposa (gateway to Yosemite)\n\n**DAY 9 (Aug 2): Yosemite National Park - Day 1**\n- Distance: 50 miles to park | Driving Time: 1.5 hours\n- Route: CA-140 into Yosemite Valley\n- Hikes & Attractions:\n  * Valley View Trail (2 miles, easy, 1 hour) - classic valley views\n  * Bridalveil Fall (0.5 miles, easy, 30 min)\n  * Yosemite Falls Trail (7.2 miles, strenuous, 4-5 hours) OR Lower Falls (1.5 miles, moderate, 1.5 hours)\n  * Glacier Point scenic drive (30 min drive, panoramic views)\n- Overnight: Yosemite Valley Lodge\n\n**DAY 10 (Aug 3): Yosemite National Park - Day 2 & Redwoods**\n- Morning: Yosemite\n  * Mirror Lake Loop (5 miles, easy, 2 hours)\n  * Sentinel Dome or Four Mile Trail\n- Afternoon: Drive toward Redwoods (280 miles, 5 hours)\n- Route: CA-120 East to I-5 North to US-101 North\n- Overnight: Eureka, California (Redwood region)\n\n**DAY 11 (Aug 4): Redwood National & State Parks**\n- Distance: 60 miles | Driving Time: 2 hours\n- Route: US-101 North through old-growth redwood groves\n- Stops & Hikes:\n  * Newton B. Drury Scenic Parkway (10 miles, 1 hour drive through ancient redwoods)\n  * Tall Trees Grove Trail (4.5 miles, moderate, 2.5 hours) - tallest trees on Earth\n  * Fern Canyon Trail (4 miles, easy-moderate, 1.5 hours) - lush fern-covered canyon\n  * Gold Bluffs Beach scenic stop\n- Overnight: Crescent City or Klamath, California\n\n**DAY 12 (Aug 5): Oregon Coast to Seattle**\n- Distance: 380 miles | Driving Time: 6 hours\n- Route: US-101 North through Oregon coast to I-5 North to Seattle\n- Stops: Crater Lake viewpoint (optional detour), Oregon Dunes scenic areas\n- Arrival: Seattle, Washington\n- Evening: Explore Pike Place Market, waterfront\n\n**TOTAL TRIP STATISTICS:**\n- Total Driving Distance: ~2,400 miles\n- Total Driving Time: ~42 hours\n- National Parks: Arches, Canyonlands, Yosemite, Redwood\n- State Parks: Valley of the Gods, Dead Horse Point, Point Lobos, Big Sur\n- Scenic Drives: Pacific Coast Highway (CA-1), Glacier Point Road, Newton B. Drury Parkway\n- Estimated Hiking: 20+ miles total across all days\n\n**PACKING ESSENTIALS:**\n- Layers (desert heat 35-37°C, coastal cool 18-24°C, mountain cool 15-20°C)\n- Hiking boots, sunscreen, hat, sunglasses\n- Camera for scenic photography\n- Cooler for snacks/drinks during long drives", "recipient_id": -1}]}
INFO:root:Agent 1 (California Coastal Route & Parks Planner) wrote output: **12-DAY DENVER TO SEATTLE CALIFORNIA COASTAL ROADTRIP ITINERARY**
**July 25 - August 5, 2026**

**DAY 1 (July 25): Denver to Moab, Utah**
- Distance: 440 miles | Driving Time: 6.5 hours
- Route: I-70 West through Colorado
- Stops: Colorado National Monument (scenic viewpoint, 30 min)
- Overnight: Moab, Utah
- Activities: Explore downtown Moab, sunset at Dead Horse Point State Park

**DAY 2 (July 26): Moab - Arches & Canyonlands**
- Distance: Local exploration (50 miles)
- Arches National Park: Devil's Garden Trail (3 hours, moderate), Delicate Arch sunset hike
- Canyonlands National Park: Island in the Sky scenic drive (1.5 hours)
- Overnight: Moab

**DAY 3 (July 27): Moab to Las Vegas via Utah Parks**
- Distance: 350 miles | Driving Time: 5 hours
- Route: US-191 South to I-70 West
- Stops: Valley of the Gods scenic drive (1 hour), Monument Valley viewpoint
- Overnight: Las Vegas, Nevada

**DAY 4 (July 28): Las Vegas to San Diego**
- Distance: 330 miles | Driving Time: 5 hours
- Route: I-15 South through Mojave Desert
- Stops: Cajon Pass scenic views, Victorville roadside attractions
- Overnight: San Diego, California
- Activities: Sunset Cliffs Natural Park, Gas Lamp Quarter exploration

**DAY 5 (July 29): San Diego Exploration**
- Distance: Local (30 miles)
- Attractions: Balboa Park museums, USS Midway Museum, La Jolla Cove (sea lions, snorkeling)
- Torrey Pines State Natural Reserve: coastal hiking trail (2 hours)
- Overnight: San Diego

**DAY 6 (July 30): San Diego to Big Sur via Los Angeles**
- Distance: 280 miles | Driving Time: 5 hours
- Route: I-5 North to US-101 North (Pacific Coast Highway begins)
- Stops: Laguna Beach scenic overlooks, Hearst Castle viewpoint
- Overnight: Carmel-by-the-Sea (near Big Sur)
- Evening: Explore charming Carmel village

**DAY 7 (July 31): Big Sur Scenic Drive & Hiking**
- Distance: 90 miles (scenic drive) | Driving Time: 3-4 hours
- Route: CA-1 (Pacific Coast Highway) - one of world's most scenic drives
- Stops & Hikes:
  * Pfeiffer Beach (purple sand, 1 hour)
  * McWay Falls Trail (0.8 miles, easy, 1 hour) - iconic waterfall
  * Bixby Bridge (historic 1932 bridge, photo stop)
  * Point Lobos State Natural Reserve (2-3 hours hiking)
- Overnight: Monterey, California

**DAY 8 (Aug 1): Monterey & Yosemite Approach**
- Distance: 130 miles | Driving Time: 2.5 hours
- Morning: Monterey Bay Aquarium, Cannery Row exploration
- Route: US-101 South to CA-152 East toward Yosemite
- Overnight: Mariposa (gateway to Yosemite)

**DAY 9 (Aug 2): Yosemite National Park - Day 1**
- Distance: 50 miles to park | Driving Time: 1.5 hours
- Route: CA-140 into Yosemite Valley
- Hikes & Attractions:
  * Valley View Trail (2 miles, easy, 1 hour) - classic valley views
  * Bridalveil Fall (0.5 miles, easy, 30 min)
  * Yosemite Falls Trail (7.2 miles, strenuous, 4-5 hours) OR Lower Falls (1.5 miles, moderate, 1.5 hours)
  * Glacier Point scenic drive (30 min drive, panoramic views)
- Overnight: Yosemite Valley Lodge

**DAY 10 (Aug 3): Yosemite National Park - Day 2 & Redwoods**
- Morning: Yosemite
  * Mirror Lake Loop (5 miles, easy, 2 hours)
  * Sentinel Dome or Four Mile Trail
- Afternoon: Drive toward Redwoods (280 miles, 5 hours)
- Route: CA-120 East to I-5 North to US-101 North
- Overnight: Eureka, California (Redwood region)

**DAY 11 (Aug 4): Redwood National & State Parks**
- Distance: 60 miles | Driving Time: 2 hours
- Route: US-101 North through old-growth redwood groves
- Stops & Hikes:
  * Newton B. Drury Scenic Parkway (10 miles, 1 hour drive through ancient redwoods)
  * Tall Trees Grove Trail (4.5 miles, moderate, 2.5 hours) - tallest trees on Earth
  * Fern Canyon Trail (4 miles, easy-moderate, 1.5 hours) - lush fern-covered canyon
  * Gold Bluffs Beach scenic stop
- Overnight: Crescent City or Klamath, California

**DAY 12 (Aug 5): Oregon Coast to Seattle**
- Distance: 380 miles | Driving Time: 6 hours
- Route: US-101 North through Oregon coast to I-5 North to Seattle
- Stops: Crater Lake viewpoint (optional detour), Oregon Dunes scenic areas
- Arrival: Seattle, Washington
- Evening: Explore Pike Place Market, waterfront

**TOTAL TRIP STATISTICS:**
- Total Driving Distance: ~2,400 miles
- Total Driving Time: ~42 hours
- National Parks: Arches, Canyonlands, Yosemite, Redwood
- State Parks: Valley of the Gods, Dead Horse Point, Point Lobos, Big Sur
- Scenic Drives: Pacific Coast Highway (CA-1), Glacier Point Road, Newton B. Drury Parkway
- Estimated Hiking: 20+ miles total across all days

**PACKING ESSENTIALS:**
- Layers (desert heat 35-37°C, coastal cool 18-24°C, mountain cool 15-20°C)
- Hiking boots, sunscreen, hat, sunglasses
- Camera for scenic photography
- Cooler for snacks/drinks during long drives
